# Day 41: Building HTML with JavaScript

**Date:** [Insert Date]

**Topics Covered:**
1. Creating new nodes: `document.createElement()`.
2. Adding content: `appendChild()` and `append()`.
3. Removing elements: `remove()` and `removeChild()`.
4. Manipulating CSS classes via `classList` (`add`, `remove`, `toggle`).

**Learning Summary:**
Today I learned that we don't always write HTML manually. In modern apps (like a To-Do list), elements are created dynamically when a user acts. I used `createElement` to make a new `div` and `appendChild` to add it to the body. I also learned how to toggle classes to create effects (like Dark Mode) without rewriting CSS rules.

**Code Snippet:**
```javascript
function addTask() {
    // 1. Create a new List Item
    const newItem = document.createElement("li");
    newItem.innerText = "Learn Fetch API";
    newItem.classList.add("task-style"); // Add CSS class

    // 2. Add delete button to it
    const delBtn = document.createElement("button");
    delBtn.innerText = "X";
    delBtn.onclick = function() {
        newItem.remove(); // Removes the element
    };

    newItem.appendChild(delBtn);

    // 3. Attach to the main list
    document.getElementById("taskList").appendChild(newItem);
}
